title: ICE: parallel compiler: `value must be in cache after waiting`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: WG-compiler-parallel
labels.description: Working group working on parallelizing the compiler

body:
### Code You need parallel compiler config for this! `rustc -Zdump-mir-dir=dir -Zthreads=306 --crate-type lib` ```Rust // build-fail // #![crate_type="rlib"] #![allow(warnings)] #[export_name="fail"] pub fn a() { } #[export_name="fail"] pub fn b() { //~^ symbol `fail` is already defined } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` 4a59ba4d54a3ec0d8ea1e82b7eeb5c8b0162de04 ``` ### Error output ``` error: symbol `fail` is already defined --> /home/matthias/vcs/github/rust_debug_assertions/tests/ui/duplicate/dupe-symbols-1.rs:12:1 | 12 | pub fn b() { | ^^^^^^^^^^ ```
